## Code Navigation — Scope MCP

This project is indexed with Scope for structural code intelligence, accessible via MCP tools.
Use the scope_* tools directly — do NOT use Bash to run scope commands.

### Available tools

| Tool | Purpose | When to use |
|------|---------|-------------|
| `scope_status` | Check index health | First, to verify scope is available |
| `scope_map` | Repo overview (~500 tokens) | Start of complex tasks |
| `scope_sketch` | Symbol structure, methods, deps | Before editing any class/function |
| `scope_summary` | One-line overview (~30 tokens) | Quick "what is this?" check |
| `scope_source` | Full source of a symbol | After sketch, when ready to read |
| `scope_find` | Search by intent | Finding code you can't name |
| `scope_refs` | All references to a symbol | Before changing signatures |
| `scope_callers` | Callers (transitive with depth) | Blast radius analysis |
| `scope_deps` | What a symbol depends on | Understanding prerequisites |
| `scope_trace` | Entry points → symbol paths | Bug tracing |
| `scope_flow` | Paths between any two symbols | Understanding connections |
| `scope_diff` | Symbols in git-changed files | PR review |

### Workflow

1. `scope_status` — verify index is fresh
2. `scope_map` — understand architecture
3. `scope_sketch` — drill into specific symbols
4. Read source only for files you'll edit
5. **3-tool rule**: if you've called 3 scope tools without editing, start editing
